commit.message:
address: fix buffer overflow

Update tests to work on Debian 11.

Accept CRLF and LF in HTTP headers, fix buffer overflow error.

As per RFC 7230, section 3.5, the recipient MAY recognize a single LF as
a line terminator and ignore any preceding CR for the start-line and header
fields.

This feature is optional by HTTP specification, but it simplifies the
scanning algorithm. Now we need to check for single character instead of
two.

Also fix buffer overflow, which happens when data length is 0 (empty
packet). This can be verified by simply putting assert(*len != 0) in
next_header() function and by executing the tests `make check` afterwards.

Signed-off-by: Oldřich Jedlička <oldium.pro@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Don't define http_protocol and tls_protocol variables multiple times.

As of gcc 10, the code generator emits globals without explicit initializer
from .bss to .data, leading to:

ld: listener.o:(.rodata+0x60): multiple definition of `http_protocol'; http.o:(.data.rel.ro.local+0x0): first defined here
ld: tls.o:(.data.rel.ro.local+0x0): multiple definition of `tls_protocol'; listener.o:(.rodata+0x68): first defined here
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status

build: add Wextra and Wpedantic and disable strict-aliasing

Libev conflicts with strict-aliasing rules, so disable strict-aliasing.
This allows us to enable more warnings.

commit.message: 0.6.0 release
tests: uninitialized memory and unused result
connection: obtain listener reference early

arch: break circular dependency between modules

Break circular dependency between listener and connection modules by
introducing listener accept_cb function pointer. This will allow reuse
of listener module with stats feature.
tests: make transparent proxy test Linux specific
tests: use /usr/bin/env perl
const and c11 config parser
Cleanup protocol definitions

config: fix config without trailing newline

Fix config parser to handle case where configuration end with a block
without a following newline e.g.:

    table foo {
      ...
    }<EOF>

The finalize() routine wouldn't be called and the block wouldn't be
honored. Tested with config_test by modifying default configuration.

commit.message:
Enable TCP keepalive on the listen socket

Without using TCP keepalive, client connections that are not closed
correctly linger behind forever, eventually exhausting the open files
limit, causing new connections to fail.
